descriptionHtml:
[center][size=5][img]http://static-5.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/69880-0-1442783280.jpg[/img]
[b]Minidresses Collection for UUNP Bodyslide 
[/b][/size]
[size=3]UNP Minidresses Collection was designed and textured by "[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/users/3347902][u][color=#0066cc]tiwa44[/color][/u][/url]"[/size]

[b]The meshes here are Re-Mastered by "[/b][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/users/2205977][u][size=4]Gamefever[/size][/u][/url][b]" to give the end-user a form fitting outfit for all body types in the UUNP System.

Tools used by "[/b] [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/users/2205977][u]gamefever[/u][/url] [b]"
[/b][size=3]BodySlide 2 and Outfit Studio[/size][b] by [/b][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/users/3330686][u][size=3]Caliente[/size][/u][/url] [b]and [/b][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/users/4291759][u][size=3]Ousnius[/size][/u][/url] [b]
Blender
Nifskope
Meshrigger[/b][b][/b][/center][b]
[/b]


[size=4][b][u]Features [/u][/b]
[/size]
[img]http://static-8.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/69880-0-1442788321.jpg[/img]

Fit them to any UNP variant, UNPB variant, Sevenbase variant, Demonfet, Saraphim, Top Model, Dream Girl, Venus....50 bodies all perfectly everytime each time.

Full Physics Weight Painting and Non-Physics Options.
No Clipping
Skin Tight Leggings, Hosery, and Undies
Racemenu Morph Support
Make any type of UNP body variant in seconds without any fuss.
Slide the outfits to fit any UNP body in  Bodyslide or Slide it in real time in game with Racemenu Morphs Pluggin
Slide your favorite outfit today with total confidence that it will work everytime with a Gamefever UUNP slider.

"Lazyboy" Solution, in downloads section.  This file answers the question statement, "I don't know how to bodyslide.?"
-No problemo
-Players can play immediately
-Use Racemenu Morphs to get the body they want in game, rather than learn all about how to use Bodyslide.
[size=4]
[/size][size=4][u]
Requirements

[/u][/size][size=3]Bodyslide Outfit Studio 2.0 [/size][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/49015/][u][size=3]http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/49015/[/size][/u][/url][size=3]?
->Be sure to install the UUNP Racemenu Option[/size][size=3]
XPMS Extended (for Morph menu in game and skeleton of course) [/size][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/68000/][u][size=3]http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/68000/[/size][/u][/url][size=3]?[/size]
[size=3]
[b][u]Recommended
[/u][/b][size=2]RaceMenu: [/size][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/29624/][u][color=#0066cc]http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/29624/
[/color][/u][/url]HDT Physics Extensions [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/53996/][u][color=#0066cc]http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/53996/[/color][/u][/url]
OR
Full Physics Kit (in downloads section, comes with my specially prepared femalehead mesh acts like HavokObject)

[/size][size=4][b][u]
Installation
[/u][/b]
Requires [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/users/3347902][u][color=#0066cc]tiwa44[/color][/u][/url]'s original mod installed first, here [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/47376/]http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/47376/[/url]?
[u]
[/u][/size][size=3]
[b][u]Mod Compatibility

[/u][/b]-To get the most from this slider set end-user should download the original mod.
-The original mod contains ESP files that make changes to Vanilla Skyrim, Dawngaurd, and Dragonborn Outfits.  This means that you may need to use WyreBash or TesVedit to create a Patch to ensure compatibility with your other files such as Overhaul Mods.
-It should go without saying that if you use Skyre or Perma you will have to run the associated Patcher for those mods.


[b][u]Known Issue's

[/u][/b]-All "Mirak Robes" from all mods that modify that mesh have "translucent" appearance in Bodyslide due to the Vanilla Games Texture for this Robe.  Most Texture replacers also replicate that "translucent appearance." The robes in this pack should be not see through in game but its reliant on your Texture Pack replacer.  I use Amideanborn Book of Armor's pack and its fine.

-Some Robes have clipping when using my highly tuned XML bounce kit.  If I fix that issue, then the fit wont be as tight for less bouncy HDT XML replacers.

-Without Tiwa44's original mod installed end-user wont get all the replacer meshes.  Also some parts may appear "blue" without the texture pack Tiwa44 made to go along with the dresses.

-Use of "3rd Party" mod's to force all NPC's in game to "Morph" is not entirely supported feature here.  That is entirely dependant on that "3rd Partie's" mod, and its functionality, capacity to change NPC, and other functions are all the responsibility of said "3rd Party."  Sorry if this is inconvenient, this file is merely a slider set that enables such feature to even be possible and more to the point its about making the outfits available for a larger amount of people.


[b][u]Credits[/u][/b]
[/size]
